nstrument and shall continue to occupy the Property as Borrower=E2=80=99s p=
rincipal residence for at least one year after the date of occupancy,=E2=80=
=9D but after that I can rent it out.) But if it=E2=80=99s me =E2=80=94 if =
I keep title to the house =E2=80=94 you might be nervous about giving me th=
at $100,000 down payment: You are kind of like a renter but with a big up-f=
ront cost. I don=E2=80=99t know how the taxes would work: Would I lose my m=
ortgage interest deduction? Would you *get* a mortgage interest deduction? =
Would your payments to me be taxable income? Lots of problems.


