JnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDkxMyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cBb08537ba" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">  accredited investors</a>.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is, I think, fairly obviously a securitie=
s offering? And you will get in trouble if you sell the shares to the publi=
c and do not register the sales with the US Securities and Exchange Commiss=
ion.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But let=E2=80=99s change the hypothetical slig=
htly. Let=E2=80=99s change how the shares work, in the following three ways=
:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You don=E2=80=99t call them =E2=80=9C=
shares.=E2=80=9D Call them =E2=80=9Ctokens.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">You don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>actually=C2=A0</em>promise ho=
lders any of the money you make. You say =E2=80=9Cif this series is a big h=
it and spawns years of sequels, the value of these tokens will go up.=E2=80=
=9D=C2=A0<em>Why=C2=A0</em>will they go up? Oh, I don=E2=80=99t know, why d=
oes anything go up? In 2021 you could just=C2=A0<em>do=C2=A0</em>this; you =
could say =E2=80=9Cthe tokens of this project will go up if the project is =
popular,=E2=80=9D even if holders of the tokens are not entitled to any of =
the project=E2=80=99s revenue.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Eac=
h token comes with a picture of one of the cats attached.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>a securities offeri=
ng? Man, I don=E2=80=99t know. There are arguments both ways:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Yes: Look, this is raising money to fi=
nance a project by selling bits of the project to investors who hope to ear=
n a speculative return. That is just classically <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32699780.289424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMDYvdGhlLXNlYy1jb21lcy1mb3ItY3J5cHR=
vP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA5MTMyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT=
1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDkxMyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cBc626a2b3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  a security</a>, =E2=80=9Can investme=
nt of money in a common enterprise with profits to come solely from the eff=
orts of others.=E2=80=9D From the investors=E2=80=99 perspective, this trad=
e is the same as selling shares.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">N=
o: There is no actual direct promise of profits! The tokens come with pictu=
res of cats! They are just art, man! This is like Walt Disney raising money=
 to make Mickey Mouse cartoons by selling drawings of the mouse! Sure those=
 drawings will be worth more if Mickey Mouse is a huge hit and spawns an an=
imation and theme-park empire, but any artist=E2=80=99s work will be more v=
aluable if the artist becomes famous, and that doesn=E2=80=99t make the art=
 a security.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/32699780.289424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDgtMjgvbG9hbnMtc3RpbGwtYXJlbi10LXNlY3VyaXRpZXM_Y21=
