<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The week before FTX Trading Ltd. filed for ban=
kruptcy last November, its then-chief executive officer, Sam Bankman-Fried,=
 sent out a sort of hacked-together balance sheet to potential investors. I=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32699780.289424/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTQvZnR4=
LXMtYmFsYW5jZS1zaGVldC13YXMtYmFkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA5MTMyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9=
tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDkxMyZ1dG1fY2=
FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB001c501c" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  made =
fun of that balance sheet</a>, which was not prepared in accordance with ge=
nerally accepted accounting principles or formatted anything like a traditi=
onal balance sheet, and which had an entry for =E2=80=9CHidden, poorly inte=
rnally labeled =E2=80=98fiat@=E2=80=99 account=E2=80=9D with a balance of n=
egative $8 billion. But it did more or less show the financial position of =
FTX, which was roughly:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">$16.9 billion of customer liabilities,=
 consisting of $8.9 billion of =E2=80=9Cliabilities=E2=80=9D and an extra $=
8 billion of =E2=80=9Chidden, poorly internally labeled =E2=80=98fiat@=E2=
=80=99 account,=E2=80=9D which you presumably add to the liabilities;</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">$9.5 billion of assets, consisting lar=
gely of weird crypto stuff that was maybe not worth quite as much as Bankma=
n-Fried thought; and</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">a howling voi=
d of almost $8 billion.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So, you know, bad. Anyway FTX went bankrupt, B=
ankman-Fried <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32699=
780.289424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjIt=
MTItMTMvaG93LXRvLWRvLWZyYXVkLWF0LWEtZnV0dXJlcy1leGNoYW5nZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwOTE=
zMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG=
1fdGVybT0yMzA5MTMmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
1f409599" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;">  was arrested</a>, a new CEO named John Ray came in to c=
lean things up, and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/clic=
k/32699780.289424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzL=
zIwMjItMTEtMTcvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1mdHgtd2FzLW5vdC12ZXJ5LWNh=
cmVmdWw_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkxMzIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc29=
1cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwOTEzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB949b9409" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  he got really mad</a> about how=
 bad FTX=E2=80=99s books and records were. =E2=80=9CNever in my career have=
 I seen such a complete failure of corporate controls and such a complete a=
bsence of trustworthy financial information as occurred here,=E2=80=9D he s=
aid, and his career included running Enron after=C2=A0its=C2=A0bankruptcy. =
Nobody knew what FTX=E2=80=99s assets were! Nobody even knew how much it ow=
ed to customers!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ray has spent the ensuing months expensively=
=C2=A0tracking down FTX=E2=80=99s assets and reviewing customer and other c=
laims. This week Ray=E2=80=99s team <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/32699780.289424/aHR0cHM6Ly9yZXN0cnVjdHVyaW5nLnJhLmtyb2xsL=
mNvbS9GVFgvSG9tZS1Eb3dubG9hZFBERj9pZDE9TWpVeE9ESTNPQT09JmlkMj0tMQ/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cB8389b590" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> filed a presentation</a> for an update t=
hat it gave to creditors, and one interesting fact about it is that it kind=
 of ties to Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s horror balance sheet from last November=
?</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9CAs of August 24, approximatel=
y 36,075 customer claims have been filed for a total of $16 billion,=E2=80=
=9D says slide 8. Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s balance sheet got to about $17 bi=
llion. Incidentally a footnote to Ray=E2=80=99s number says that it =E2=80=
=9Cexcludes 193 customer claims facially frivolous or errant of ~$9.2 quint=
illion,=E2=80=9D and I suppose the FTX bankruptcy is naturally going to dra=
w out a few people who are like =E2=80=9Coh yes FTX very much owes me one q=
uintillion dollars,=E2=80=9D sure.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;"=
>Slide 10 has a fun little thermometer showing how many assets FTX has reco=
vered so far; it is up to about $7 billion. Bankman-Fried had $9.5 billion,=
 but even he realized that a lot of his numbers were fake. His balance shee=
t included $2.2 billion of Serum tokens; Ray notes (slide 24) that =E2=80=
=9Cthe Debtors=E2=80=99 crypto holdings include certain tokens that fail to=
 meet liquidity thresholds and/or are largely controlled by the estate=E2=
=80=9D =E2=80=94 =E2=80=9CSamcoins,=E2=80=9D they used to be called, tokens=
 that Bankman-Fried had helped invent, that were mostly owned by FTX and th=
at lost a lot of value after Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s fall. Ray values the S=
erum stash at $362 million, which is probably still generous.</li>=09<li st=
yle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">On the other hand Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s balan=
ce sheet did not include $200 million of Bahamas real estate, because at th=
at point =E2=80=94=C2=A0while Bankman-Fried was trying to raise rescue fina=
ncing and also not get in trouble for losing/stealing billions of dollars o=
f customer money =E2=80=94=C2=A0it would not have been a great look to be l=
ike =E2=80=9Cwell we misplaced $8 billion of customer funds but man do we o=
wn a lot of luxury apartments.=E2=80=9D Ray has no such qualms, and include=
s (slide 17) pictures of the real estate, a map, and a total appraised valu=
e of $199 million.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">That still leav=
es a hole of, you know, $9 billion-ish.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And I am only really looking at customer claim=
s; in fact, Ray reports (slide 7) that there is a surprising $65 billion of=
 other claims outstanding, consisting mostly of a $43.5 billion tax claim f=
rom the US Internal Revenue Service. =E2=80=9CAssumed to be subordinated,=
=E2=80=9D says the slide, and it is hard to imagine how the IRS could reall=
y demand $43.5 billion in income taxes from a company whose actual lifetime=
 income appears to have been negative.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ray=E2=80=99s next steps include selling=C2=A0=
a bunch of the crypto.=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.=
com/click/32699780.289424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY29pbmRlc2suY29tL21hcmtldHMvMjAyM=
y8wOS8xMi9jcnlwdG9jdXJyZW5jeS1hbHRjb2luLWNyYXNoLWlzLWNvbWluZy1tYXRyaXhwb3J0=
Lw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBedc78e36" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Coindesk reports</a> that =
=E2=80=9CAt least $3.4 billion worth of crypto is likely to be sold by FTX =
so it can return fiat currency to its users instead of tokens, which should=
 create an overhang for altcoins for the rest of the year, Matrixport said =
in a report Monday.=E2=80=9D FTX=E2=80=99s crypto holdings are largely =E2=
=80=9Caltcoins=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0there=E2=80=99s $560 million of Bitc=
oin and $192 million of Ether, but there=E2=80=99s a lot more Solana, and m=
ore Serum than you=E2=80=99d want =E2=80=94=C2=A0and it is a big holder of =
them; its selling will be bad for prices.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another next step is restarting FTX? I mean? I=
t <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32699780.289424/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDEtMTkvZnR=
4LWlzLXBsYW5uaW5nLWEtY29tZWJhY2s_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkxMzIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX2=
1lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwOTEzJnV0bV9jY=
W1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBeb74f9cc" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  still =
seems</a> like a wild idea to me. But slide 36 is an =E2=80=9CFTX 2.0 Proce=
ss Update,=E2=80=9D saying that Ray=E2=80=99s team will =E2=80=9Cconsider v=
arying potential structures, including an acquisition, merger, recapitaliza=
tion or other transaction to relaunch the FTX.com and/or FTX US exchanges.=
=E2=80=9D They contacted =E2=80=9C75+ potential bidders,=E2=80=9D including=
 =E2=80=9Cexisting exchanges,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Cstrategic buyers=E2=80=9D a=
nd =E2=80=9Cfinancial buyers,=E2=80=9D got some bids, and admitted some bid=
ders to a =E2=80=9CRound 2 process=E2=80=9D that involves =E2=80=9Cextensiv=
e bidder diligence &amp; bi-lateral info sharing.=E2=80=9D So maybe FTX wil=
l come back.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When Bankman-Fried was circulating his despera=
tion balance sheet, he was well aware that it showed a gaping hole of almos=
t $8 billion of negative equity, but he nonetheless thought that some inves=
tor might see that balance sheet and decide to invest: The investor might s=
ay =E2=80=9Cwell, you have $17 billion of liabilities and $9 billion of ass=
ets, which is bad, but I will put in the $8 billion you need to fill the ho=
le because you have a=C2=A0<em>good business</em>, and if I can keep it ali=
ve and revive its reputation then I can earn billions of dollars a year in =
trading fees, which will make that $8 billion a good investment.=E2=80=9D O=
n a pure balance-sheet basis FTX owed a lot more money than it had, but as =
a going concern maybe it was a good investment.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or that was the idea. You might object: <em>Is=
 </em>it such a good business, after misplacing all that customer money? In=
 any case,=C2=A0Bankman-Fried could not actually convince anyone of it, but=
 he did not have a lot of time, and at that point he was maybe not the best=
 person to pitch it. Ray has more time. I am not convinced he is the best p=
erson to pitch it either =E2=80=94=C2=A0he has been pretty negative about F=
TX! =E2=80=94=C2=A0but he might as well give it a shot.</p>
